Therefore, the philosophy of participation of RESs in frequency has been changed. Recently, new grid codes state that RESs must participate in frequency regulation which will be discussed in detail in Sect. 4. In Germany, for example, if the power system frequency increased to 50.2 Hz, the RESs must decrease their output by a rate of 40% of their capacity per Hz [58]. On the other hand, some papers have been conducted to determine the allowable penetration level of RESs especially wind energy such as [59, 60]. The flow chart in Fig. 5 describes a criterion for calculating the acceptable level of RESs while achieving the standard Fnadir\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
